description: EMERGENCY DISTRESS SALE!!! 6,000 OBO AS IS We are in the process of an urgent move and under a MASSIVE time crunch, which is reflected in our asking price. Le Pecheur De'Toilles (Fisherman of the Stars) is 60' long with a 17.5 foot beam and a 7.5 foot draft. Built in 1955, in Nova Scotia, as a North Atlantic fishing trawler, she was converted for private use in the late 60's. She has 11 layers of fiberglass laid over her oak hull. She has a 1933 (older than the boat!) 6 cylinder Caterpillar diesel engine, that starts and runs like a champ every time we've tried, and qualifies her for vintage vessel registration. There is a problem with the transmission, work will need to be done to get her self propelled again but there is room to put an outboard on back as an option or in the interim.  She has new starter batteries (may need to be charged, not sure), 1,000 gallon fuel tank, 700 gallon fresh water tank, new water pump, water-maker (membranes need pickling), and electric windlass with new batteries. On board diesel generator needs new alternator and fresh water pump (around $700 from Marathon Diesel). Below deck are the main living quarters: The large V-birth has 4 bunks, 2 full length closets and a curtain that separates it from the bunk area directly aft.  Centerline is an open communal area with a double-wide bunk on either side, both with a privacy curtain and storage underneath. Amidships is a grand salon. U-shaped settees, perfect for lounging, are on the port-side and a table with benches, desk and a freezer (compressor needs work) on starboard. Aft of the saloon there is a head with a shower on starboard, and the master stateroom, with drawers, hanging storage and storage under the bed, on port. Further aft is the sizable engine room and 'crawl-in' lazarette. These are both only accessible from the pilot-house. The deck is flat and massive, perfect to play fetch with the dogs or host raucous pirate parties. There is a sampson post a few feet from the bow, just forward of the electric windlass. Aft is a massive hatch that floods the bunk area with light below, when not covered so lazy pirates can sleep in. Aft of that is the forward mast. Amidships is the companionway door. Our favorite place to star-gaze is from the hammock strung between the mast and companionway.  Between the companionway and the wheel-house/galley/full head, is a large open area with a giant alfresco table and propane grill. The raised wheel-house is centerline, accessible through the galley, whose door is port of the wheel-house. The galley has plenty of seating, large table, full propane oven, large top-loading fridge (compressor needs work) mini-fridge/freezer, microwave, double sink and lots of storage. Stairs down to the engine room and lazarette are just inside the galley door. Engine room has the space for an additional stateroom (In it's past was used as Captain's quarter's) Starboard of the wheel-house/galley is another full head, with composting toilet. She is jam-packed with character and personality! People admire and comment on her daily. She has the potential to be an excellent investment vessel; You could make a killing in Key West with sunset sails, for example. Formerly, she hosted an Outward Bound type program in the Bahamas, for about 17 years. Or, you can just embrace the Pirate-Life, like we have. We have lived aboard with our family of 5, 2 dogs, and 2 cats comfortably, for quite a while. She needs some love, for sure, but most importantly, her hull is sound. I like to say that she is a Home-Depot boat, not a Westmarine boat, which makes repairs and upgrades much more affordable. Fixed up and with a patient seller, she could easily demand $100K(+) Contact my husband John by phone @ show contact info
title: 60ft Motor Sailer/Pirateship

description: Carver 355 35 foot ACMY (Aft Cabin Motor Yacht) 1998 "Flyin Low" Sale includes a 2004 Avon 10'2" inflatable tender with a fiberglass bottom and 8 HP Johnson outboard. Tender will plane and both tender and outboard are in excellent condition. Please visit www. FlyinLowSale.com for more information & pictures. Diesel Powered by Cummins 330 B twin engines Port engine has 525 hrs and is a Cummins Reman installed, sea trialed, warranted, and certified by Cummins in November 2013. Starboard engine is original and has 1830 hrs. Generator is a Westerbeke 7.6 KW diesel with 890 hrs. All maintenance performed on Flyin Low since I purchased it in 2010 is documented and records are available for viewing. This is a wonderful family cruiser with all the amenities needed for weekend or extended cruising. The two stateroom and two head layout with a wide open salon and dining area was very popular for Carver Yachts. The flybridge has seating for six, the aft deck is perfect for lounging and the molded in steps provide access to the water. Factory hard top over sundeck and aluminum frame covered with herculon over fly bridge. Throughout this 355, you'll find that the 13' 3" wide beam allows for a remarkable amount of space and comfort for a craft this size. The fly bridge provides plenty of seating plus complete instrumentation at the control console. There's a forward bridge lounge, plus a sliding pilot seat and companion seating as well as plenty of storage. The hardtop, electronics arch and enclosure, offers a superb spot for entertaining or relaxing. The Euro-style transom with staircase-style steps provides easier, more convenient boarding. Electronics: • Raymaine touch screen E90W MFD plotter with color Radar and video feed (4) of engines and vacuum gauges. Installed 2013. • Garmin touch screen 720 plotter. • Standard Horizon GX 2100 VHF radio with AIS (displays on E90W) and DSC with hailer. • Raymaine ST-50 Tridata depth which also displays on Garmin and Raymaine Plotters. • Raymarine p70R autopilot connected to Ray MFD via Sea Talk with tracking capability. Installed 2014. Electrical: • Westerbeke 7.6 KW generator • 3 battery bank DC electrical system, House, Engine Start, Generator Start • All 6 batteries are AGM's. 4 House batteries, 1 Engine Start and 1 Generator Start • All Battery banks monitored by digital volt meter with bank selector switch. • Victron Battery Monitor on house battery bank • 1500 Watt inverter * 30 Amp 3 bank Charles Marine Battery Charger Engines: • Both raw water pumps upgraded to SBMar units. • Borel hi temp raw water alarms monitor both engines. • Boost gauges monitor turbo output pressure. • Engine & Generator oil change pump makes changing oil a snap. • Oil changed approx. every 100 hrs. • After-coolers serviced approx. every 200 hrs. • Automatic Engine/Generator fire suppression system. Fuel System: • Racor 900 series filters with vacuum gauges. • Multi-stage filtration with Fleetguard FS-1000 filters • Squeeze bulb priming system makes fuel priming a snap. • Fuel Transfer pump with switch located on helm. Bilge & Hull: • 3 bilge pumps with float switches and manual switching at helm • Bilge hi water alarm with siren and strobe light. Electrically in parallel to a panic sw in master stateroom. • Bottom painted in April 2015 • All 3 fire extinguishers replaced Oct 2015 • Bottom cleaned monthly and zinc's maintained by Gulf Bay Divers. Interior: • Flat screen TV with DVD player in Salon. • Flat screen TV in master stateroom • AM/FM radio with Bluetooth and marine band. • Flexsteel Furniture, couch reclines with foot support. • 3 burner stove with true oven • Refrigerator runs on AC or DC. • 2 reverse cycle Air conditioning and heating units. • Vacuflush toilets in both heads • Hot/Cold pressure water. • 50 Amp AC power with 50' cord and 2 30 amp adaptors. • 3 CO detectors Sundeck: • Icerette ice maker and wet bar. • Carpeted sundeck and helm. • Blue/White selectable LED night lighting on sundeck ceiling. Additional notes; • Sundeck canvas replaced 2014 • See thru sun shield made for port and starboard side of helm and sundeck. • Delta Anchor, 50' chain, and 150' rode replaced in 2010. Windlass upgraded to a Maxwell RC-8 in 2011 • Included in price is a 2004 Avon 10' inflatable tender and 8 HP Johnson outboard motor. The tender was serviced August 2016 and the outboard motor is in good working order ready to test drive. The tender will plane with 2 people. • A weaver davit system and weaver leaver motor mount system allows for easy stowing and deployment of the tender with outboard motor attached from the swim platform. • Aluminum frame with herculon material cover the fly bridge and is completely dry. This is not a bimini. We purchased Flyin Low in 2010 and used it frequently. It did not sit idle which can cause mechanical problems. Flyin Low visited Key West, the Bahamas, and ran the entire ICW to the Chesapeake and back to Tampa Bay. It is fitted and ready to cruise and can be viewed at The Harborage Marina in St. Petersburg, FL. You will not likely find another diesel Carver 355 on the market and not at this price.
